SYNPOSIS
    set_driver_hook(hook: int, value)

DESCRIPTION
    Used to set a driver hook. The hook is identified by its integer
    value and the hook value might be any arbitary type depending on
    the hook to set.

    Deleting a driver hook is done by setting it to 'undef'.

EXAMPLE
    set_driver_hook(3, processUserInput);

    function processUserInput(token, input) {
       ...
    }

SEE ALSO
    driver/hooks
